result.execSummary:
All charges against Danielle S Brannigan in this case have been dismissed. These charges were not proven and have no legal effect. Danielle S Brannigan is presumed innocent.

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

records.addlTxt: 1:20 p.m.  Court calls case, cites appearances.  Atty Brewer appears via Zoom with Danielle Brannigan appearing via Zoom audio.  Matthew J. Tingstad appears for the State of WI.  Court provides background.  Def addresses Court.  Per Court, since def posted on MN warrant and released, no grounds for extradition hearing.  Court dismisses case.  Adj.  1:25 p.m.  klr

records.descr: Demand for Discovery and Inspection - Defendant

records.addlTxt: 1:29 p.m.   Court calls case.   Attorney Matthew J Tingstad in court for State of Wisconsin.  Danielle Brannigan in court in custody.  Here today for extradition hearing regarding warrant in Minnesota.  Court explains meaning of hearing today to the defendant.  He explains her right to an attorney and/or to get the governor involved if she does not want to waive extradition.  Defendant in distress and states she does not want to go back to Minnesota.  D.A. hands her public defender information and she states she will contact atty.  After further information from the Court as to the next steps, defendant changes her mind and states wants to go back to Minnesota.  Court states he will not allow her to waive extradition today because she is under duress right now and he wants her to talk to an attorney first.  D.A. requests a reasonable cash bond of $1,000 be set.  Court remands defendant back to the custody of the Sheriff's Dept. pending a future hearing.  Defendant is under duress and not in a position to waive extradition today.  Court sets next hearing for Monday (9/26/22) at 9:00 a.m. with public defender to attend.  Court adj. at 1:36 p.m.  wmg
